[src:breadth-first-search-algorithm/breadth-first-search] On the other hand, both depth-first algorithms typically require far less extra memory than breadth-first search.
[src:breadth-first-search-algorithm/breadth-first-search] Breadth-first search can be generalized to both undirected graphs and directed graphs with a given start node (sometimes referred to as a 'search key').
[src:breadth-first-search-algorithm/breadth-first-search] In state space search in artificial intelligence, repeated searches of vertices are often allowed, while in theoretical analysis of algorithms based on breadth-first search, precautions are typically taken to prevent repetitions.
